# LEVELGEN.md — generator, solver, difficulty

**Authority:** [LEVELGEN.md](LEVELGEN.md) — `config.js`, templates, `generator.js`, `solver.js`, `score.js`, CLI, random pool mode, distributions, batch variation, interactive designer, runtime loading of `levels.generated.js`.

## Before editing

- Read `LEVELGEN.md` for the affected subsystem (config shape, template/z-aware footprints, solver modes, scoring families, report output).

## After editing

- If you change how levels are built, validated, scored, configured, or emitted, **update `LEVELGEN.md`** (file paths, config fields, behavior, CLI, or tuning notes).
- High-level “what the game is” stays in [GAME_SPEC.md](GAME_SPEC.md); keep procedural detail here only.

## Related

- Rust solver crate under `crates/levelgen-solver` — document interface and build/test commands here when they change.
